craterdog.collections

Class List<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • craterdog.smart.SmartObject<Collection<E>>
      • craterdog.collections.abstractions.Collection<E>
        • craterdog.collections.abstractions.OpenCollection<E>
          • craterdog.collections.abstractions.SortableCollection<E>
            • craterdog.collections.List<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of element managed by the collection.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Accessible<E>, Dynamic<E>, Indexed<E>, Sortable<E>, Composite, Sequential<E>, java.lang.Comparable<Collection<E>>, java.lang.Iterable<E>

    public class List<E>
extends SortableCollection<E>
implements Indexed<E>
    This collection class implements a sortable list which performs very well for both inserts and indexed lookups of its values. The implementation dynamically scales up and down the size of the underlying data structures as the number of associations changes over time.
    Author:
    Derk Norton

        public List(java.util.Collection<? extends E> elements)
        This constructor creates a new list using the elements provided in a java collection. In general it is confusing to mix java collections with craterdog collections since the former uses zero based indexing and the latter uses positive and negative ordinal based indexing.
        Parameters:
        elements - The elements that should be used to seed the list.
